<DOC><DOCNO> AP890413-0031 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-04-13-89 0248EST</FILEID><FIRST>r i PM-Chile-Cocaine     04-13 0166</FIRST><SECOND>PM-Chile-Cocaine,0170</SECOND><HEAD>Police Raid Yacht, Seize 570 Pounds Of Cocaine</HEAD><DATELINE>TALCAHUANO, Chile (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Police raided a U.S.-registered yachtin this southern port and found 570 pounds of Miami-bound cocaine _Chile's largest seizure of the narcotic, a police general saidtoday.   Two Colombians and an Ecuadoran were arrested in the raid lateWednesday in the port 350 miles south of Santiago after residentstipped off officials that those aboard were spending large amountsof money in town, police said.   Police Gen. Rene Varas said the drug cache found aboard theFlorida-registered Marco Polo has a street value of $160 million.He said it was Chile's largest cocaine seizure.   Among those arrested was the yacht's owner and skipper, aColombian who police identified as Miguel Eduardo Taylor, 41.   The boat arrived from Colombia and was scheduled to leaveThursday or Friday for Miami, said Varas.   Among the world's largest cocaine busts was the seizure of22,000 pounds of the drug in Colombia in March 1984.</TEXT></DOC>